# MCP Capability Catalog (M1-M34)

`alc_mcp.catalog.MCP_TOOLS` is the canonical machine-readable catalog. This file is generated by `bin/render_catalogs.py`; regenerate it instead of hand-editing tool rows.

| ID | Tool | Kind | Backing | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| M1 | `get_gates` | read | `alc_query.get_gates` | Return approved gates, scoped by state-root (user/project/both) and optionally filtered by domain. |
| M2 | `get_skill_context` | read | `alc_query.get_skill_context` | Return latest skill-context markdown, scoped by state-root (user/project/both). |
| M3 | `get_recommendations` | read | `alc_query.get_recommendations` | Return recommender output rows from recommendations.json (project-scope). |
| M4 | `list_pending_patches` | read | `alc_query.get_pending_patches` | Return pending patch bundles, excluding rejected/deferred patches (project-scope). |
| M5 | `get_dashboard_url` | read | `state_handle.dashboard_url` | Return the dashboard URL for repo, preferring localhost when configured. |
| M6 | `propose_apply` | propose | `alc_propose.propose_apply` | Return an apply CLI command for a patch id without applying it (no mutation). |
| M7 | `propose_gate` | propose | `alc_propose.propose_gate` | Append an operator-proposed gate to the improvement queue for review. |
| M8 | `report_outcome` | observe | `alc_propose.report_outcome` | Record a recommendation or legacy gate outcome through event_writer. |
| M9 | `report_agent_event` | observe | `alc_propose.report_agent_event` | Record bounded agent dispatch telemetry through event_writer. |
| M10 | `exec_sandbox` | exec | `exec_sandbox.run` | Run a bounded sandbox command in read, worktree, or eval scope. |
| M11 | `next_action` | read | `alc_next_action.next_action` | Synthesise a session-lifecycle recommendation (what's next, session start/end, where I left off). |
| M12 | `get_apply_log` | read | `alc_query.get_apply_log` | Patch apply events from project-scope events.sqlite (UQ1). |
| M13 | `get_outcomes` | read | `alc_query.get_outcomes` | Eval-verdict outcomes from project-scope events.sqlite (UQ2). Lets agents check whether a previously loaded gate was helpful. |
| M14 | `get_event_dag` | read | `alc_query.get_event_dag` | Session event DAG via recursive CTE on project-scope events.sqlite (UQ5). Use to trace what happened in a specific session. |
| M15 | `get_actor_summary` | read | `alc_query.get_actor_summary` | Per-actor event counts from project-scope events.sqlite (UQ6). |
| M16 | `get_skill_invocation_history` | read | `alc_query.get_skill_invocation_history` | Historical invocation events for a specific skill from project-scope events.sqlite (UQ7). |
| M17 | `get_skill_usage_summary` | read | `alc_query.get_skill_usage_summary` | Aggregate actor_name counts in indexed events, sorted by count desc (UQ8). Used by dashboard skill-routing signals. |
| M18 | `mark_patch_status` | propose | `alc_propose.mark_patch_status` | Mark a pending patch as deferred or rejected and emit a status event (UP5). Closes the M6 propose_apply asymmetry by letting agents propose declining a patch. |
| M19 | `get_proposal_queue` | read | `alc_query.get_proposal_queue` | Return operator proposal queue rows from improvement-queue.jsonl as normalized lifecycle records (UQ10). |
| M20 | `get_proposal_lifecycle` | read | `alc_query.get_proposal_lifecycle` | Return normalized proposal lifecycle rows across queue, patch, and suggestion artifacts (UQ11). |
| M21 | `run_distill` | action | `dashboard.actions.run_distill` | Start the dashboard distill workflow and return a structured action job id. |
| M22 | `list_action_jobs` | read | `dashboard.actions.list_action_jobs` | List dashboard action jobs started through the shared action service. |
| M23 | `get_action_job` | read | `dashboard.actions.get_action_job` | Return one dashboard action job by id. |
| M24 | `get_action_state` | read | `dashboard.actions.actions_summary` | Return promoted gate and muted domain dashboard action state. |
| M25 | `promote_gate_action` | action | `dashboard.actions.promote_gate` | Promote a dashboard gate action idempotently. |
| M26 | `unpromote_gate_action` | action | `dashboard.actions.unpromote_gate` | Remove a promoted dashboard gate action. |
| M27 | `mute_domain` | action | `dashboard.actions.mute_domain` | Mute a dashboard domain idempotently. |
| M28 | `unmute_domain` | action | `dashboard.actions.unmute_domain` | Remove a dashboard domain mute. |
| M29 | `get_latest_report` | read | `dashboard.actions.latest_report` | Return structured metadata for the latest HTML or markdown dashboard report. |
| M30 | `get_session_signals` | read | `alc_next_action.get_session_signals` | Return raw synthesized session lifecycle facts without ranking decisions or prose. |
| M31 | `get_lifecycle_contracts` | read | `alc_query.get_lifecycle_contracts` | Return lifecycle contracts for core ALC entities. |
| M32 | `get_dashboard_payload` | read | `dashboard_read_model.build_dashboard_payload` | Return the exact dashboard payload used by FastAPI /api/data, including action state. |
| M33 | `get_dashboard_health` | read | `dashboard_read_model.build_dashboard_health` | Return the exact dashboard health payload used by FastAPI /api/health. |
| M34 | `get_latest_report_content` | read | `dashboard_read_model.build_latest_report_content` | Return latest dashboard report content equivalent to /api/reports/latest or /api/reports/latest.md. |

In addition to the catalog tools, the server exposes a meta tool `list_capabilities(repo)` that returns the live catalog plus per-tool `version` and `min_compatible_version`. Agents should call it first and compare against their known client contract before invoking other tools.
